INSERT INTO `dr_server_conferenceinfo` VALUES ('1859', 'International Conference on Advances in Computing, Communication & Materials', 'ICACCM', ' ', 'Dehradun, India', '2020-08-21', '2020-06-10', '2020-07-04', '', 'Paper Submission & Publication Details\r\n\r\nPapers should conform to the IEEE format and specifications. All submissions must be in English only. Authors are invited to submit full paper (Maximum 8 pages, double-column A4) as PDF using the IEEE templates. All papers should be submitted electronically through easy chair only. The material presented should be original and not published or under submission elsewhere. Accepted papers will be published by IEEE CPS and paper will be published in IEEE Xplore Digital Library. At least one author of each accepted paper is required to register and present their work at the conference; otherwise the paper will not be included in the proceedings.\r\n\r\nThe IEEE paper template can be downloaded from the link given below:\r\nhttps://www.ieee.org/conferences/publishing/ templates.html\r\n\r\nTracks(Not Limited to….)\r\n\r\nAdvance in Communication, Network & Social Network Analysis\r\nAd hoc networks for ubiquitous communications\r\nCyber laws & security\r\nSocial networks & Online Education\r\nOpen Source software in Web Technology\r\nEthical hanking Approaches\r\nMobile Computing Algorithm\r\nIntelligent Transport System\r\nSignal Processing & Digital Image Processing\r\nHigh Speed Network\r\nRF\r\nFraud Control Techniques\r\nNetwork Security & privacy policies\r\nComputation in emerging computer system\r\nSoftwaredevelopment for mobile devices\r\nNovelty in Wireless sensor networks\r\nInformation & System Security\r\nNeural Network, Virtual Reality & Web Crawlers\r\nData management for ubiquitous computing\r\nVisual representation of dynamic social networks\r\nTrust networks and evolution\r\nMisbehavior detection in communities\r\nMulti- agent based social network modeling and analysis\r\n\r\nBig Data\r\nCloud Co